A
\lambda_1 \geq \lambda_2 \geq ... \geq \lambda_n
v_1, v_2. ..., v_n
\displaystyle \max_{0\neq x\perp v_1} \Bigl({x^*Ax\over x^*x}\Bigr)
\displaystyle \max_{0\neq x\perp v_1} \Bigl({x^*Ax\over x^*x}\Bigr)=\lambda_2
x=\alpha_1 v_1 + ...+ \alpha_n v_n
v=c_2v_2+...+c_nv_n
\lambda_i\leq\lambda_2
i=2,...,n
\frac{v^\star Av}{v^\star v}= \frac{\lambda_2c_2^2+...+\lambda_nc_n^2}{c_2^2+...+c_n^2}\leq\lambda _2
v=v_2
\lambda_2=\max_{0\neq x\perp v_1}\frac{v^\star Av}{v^\star v}
